### ============================================
### Maintenance Log API - Security Testing
### ============================================

### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:7070/api/v1
@authUrl = http://localhost:7070/api/v1/auth

# Tokens will be set after login (copy from response)
@adminToken =
@managerToken =
@technicianToken =


### ============================================
### 1. AUTHENTICATION - Login & Register
### ============================================

### Login as Admin
POST {{authUrl}}/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@example.com",
  "password": "admin123"
}

### Login as Manager
POST {{authUrl}}/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "manager@example.com",
  "password": "manager123"
}

### Login as Technician
POST {{authUrl}}/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "technician@example.com",
  "password": "tech123"
}

### Login with Invalid Credentials (should fail - 401)
POST {{authUrl}}/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "wrong@example.com",
  "password": "wrongpassword"
}

### Login with Inactive User (should fail - 403)
POST {{authUrl}}/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "inactive@example.com",
  "password": "inactive123"
}

### ============================================
### 2. PROTECTED ENDPOINT TEST
### ============================================

### Access Protected Endpoint (as ADMIN) - Should succeed
GET {{authUrl}}/protected
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### Access Protected Endpoint (as MANAGER) - Should fail (403)
GET {{authUrl}}/protected
Authorization: Bearer {{managerToken}}

### Access Protected Endpoint (no token) - Should fail (401)
GET {{authUrl}}/protected

